125
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,400
population movement. Thus, modern states initiated a series of readability projects: standardizing surnames (previously many only had given names), standardizing units of measurement, land surveying and registration, censuses and household registration systems, and grid-based urban planning. On the surface, these were all advancements; they indeed improved administrative efficiency. However, the problem is that in the pursuit of readability, those unreadable but crucial elements were often

126
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:48,966
destroyed. Let me give you a

127
