shrubs and herbaceous plants. For forestry officials, this type of forest was unreadable; they couldn't accurately calculate timber reserves, predict future yields, or manage them effectively. So they invented scientific forestry. First, they cleared the existing mixed forests,

132
00:12:24,466 --> 00:12:25,433
then planted a single tree species, usually spruce, planted in neat rows with uniform spacing, and harvested simultaneously. The result was a forest that became a timber factory, appearing from the air

133
