a model for all of Europe. The second

138
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,566
generation? Disaster! Trees began to die off in large numbers, pests and diseases spread, and the soil degraded. By the second harvest cycle, yields had plummeted. What happened? Those chaotic traditional forests had complex ecosystems. Different tree species were interdependent; understory plants protected the soil; dead branches and leaves provided nutrients; and birds controlled pests. This was a balanced system that had evolved over thousands of years.

139
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,833
Monoculture

140
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:17,366
plantations destroyed this system. Without diversity, pests and diseases spread easily; without understory vegetation,

141
00:13:17,366 --> 00:13:18,833
