164
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:14,933
A farmer who has farmed for 30 years, while not understanding chemical equations, possesses the wisdom to handle specific situations. The best scenario is a combination of both: Techne provides general principles, while Metis allows for flexible

165
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,600
application in specific contexts. The worst scenario is using Techne to suppress Metis, with experts sitting

166
00:16:27,466 --> 00:16:29,000
in offices directing thousands of specific situations using standardized procedures.

167
00:16:29,133 --> 00:16:31,900
Scott summarizes four necessary conditions for the failure of high-modernism projects: First, administrative order and readability—the state needs to simplify complex social realities; second, a high-modernist ideology—believing that scientific planning is superior to traditional experience;

168
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,700
third, an authoritarian state—having the power and will to implement radical change; and finally, a lack of checks and balances—no civil

169
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,300
society or local power to resist. Disaster occurs when all four conditions are present. If any one is missing, the project may only be inefficient, not a major catastrophe. For example, urban redevelopment in the United States also has high-modernist characteristics,

170
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,733
but

171
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,933
because of a relatively active civil society, the degree of destruction is limited. In contrast, authoritarian states like the Soviet Union and Tanzania... The

